rComments: Honor homework is hard, but interesting.

He is very familiar with course content, he can always get my question even before I finish asking. He is definitely nice and loves to help. One thing I don't like about this honor section is the lack of discussion session, which could be helpful. But 241 is a inherently pretty hard course when you first encounter, he is making the learning easier

Stefan read straight off of the powerpoints quite a bit. The most alarming thing about that statement though is the word powerpoint. I don't believe that calculus should ever be taught by reading off of slides. So expect to do a lot of learning on your own because you can't really count on him. However, the tests were never that difficult.
Reads straight from the book.  Doesn't teach just shows examples.  Learn a lot more in discussion than I do in his lectures
Stephan was very unclear and did not understand his own material. He was also very rude and intimidating to ask questions of.
